HEADWORD: Deflected
<hw>De*flect"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Turned aside;
deviating from a direct line or course.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bent downward; deflexed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deflection</ent>⟦br⟧
